frameDefinitions: This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
This frame concerns people's knowledge or skill in certain domains.
The Military of a Possessor (either a nation, institution, or private individual) conducts large-scale activities in a Area to accomplish military or combined military/non-military goals.
An entity is considered worthy of mention for their ability or influence among some Type of similar entities.
This frame contains general words denoting equipment where the Use or purpose is not specified by the lexeme but (typically) by a separate expression.
The size of an Entity is assessed in terms of the Degree by which it deviates from the norm.
frameExamples: FE Layer-1: He is an <t>experienced</t> programmer.
These groups are known to have carried out attacks on international coalition forces <t>operating</t> in Afghanistan.
Dali is one of the <t>great</t> artists of the 20th century.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.
The person whose expertise is assessed.
<fen>Skill</fen> identifies the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s talent or ability to do things with one's hand or body.
The area of knowledge (as opposed to a practical skill) in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> 's experience is assessed.
A  product of behavior that shows the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s skill or lack of skill.

This frame element can only occur in place of a skill expression. It refers to the prototypical patient in an action involving the Protagonist. For instance, in the following sentence  the children are experts at some (contextually given) action such as rolling the hoops.

<fex name='Protagonist'>Some children</fex> <m>were</m> <fex name='Degree'>quite</fex> <t>expert</t> <fex name='Focal_participant'>with wooden hoops</fex>.
This frame element denotes a role in which the protagonist has developed his expertise.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Protagonist</fen> has the expertise.
The <fen>Force</fen> carries out the operation. Depending on the size of the operation, this may be as few as one individual or as large as the armed forces of a nation.
The <fen>Area</fen> in which the <fen>Military</fen> is conducting operations.
The nation, group, or situation which the operation opposes.
The <fen>Goal</fen> of the operation.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the operations are carried out.
The location of the operation.
The kind of thing which is notable. This may be an event, place, item, or role and is plural.
The name of the notable entity.
The time during which the entity is considered notable.
The geographic area in which the entity is considered notable.
The complex artifact with a particular use.
The thing whose size is being considered.
The feature of an (actual or possible) <fen>Entity</fen> that is measured. In literal examples, it essentially must be size, or a word equivalent to size such as bulk.
listRoleExamples: The Beaujolais Nouveau is dazzling <fex>in freshness</fex>.
A skillful <fex>advertising campaign</fex> persuaded voters that his opponent was soft on crime.
His prowess <fex>as a surgeon</fex> is impressive.
<fex>He</fex> died while carrying out counter-IED operations.
Operations <fex>against Afghanistan</fex> continue to be carried out.
He was captured in a covert <fex>arrest</fex> operation carried out by an elite group of highly-trained Marines.
This sort of operation should only be conducted <fex>in open areas</fex>.
Shakespeare is one of the great <fex>poets</fex>.
<fex>Shakespeare</fex> is one of the great poets.
Bob Dylan is among the most notable musicians <fex>of the 20th century</fex>.
Dumas is one of the most notable authors <fex>in France</fex>.
The particles were smaller <fex>in size</fex> than expected .
